assistance?</p><p>Call or text anytime, day or night: <a href=tel:224-410-0522>224-410-0522</a></p></div></div></nav> </div> </div> </div> </header><div class=banner-above> </div><div id=mainbody class=clearfix><div id=content><div id=message-component><div id=system-message-container> </div> </div><div id=content-area><section class=mobile-hero-img style="background-image: url(../../images/areas/hero-maryland-mobile.jpg)"></section><section class=city-hero style="background-image: url(../../images/areas/hero-maryland-desktop.jpg)"><div class=container><h1 class=title><span>Adoption in</span> Eldersburg, MD</h1></div></section><section class=loving-decision><div class=container><h3 class="title green mb-4">Birthmother Adoption Support Services in Eldersburg, MD</h3><p class=mb-5>If you are facing an unplanned pregnancy or you’ve found yourself in a position where you can no longer care for your young child, adoption is an option. Read on to learn more about placing your baby for adoption while receiving the support and guidance you need during this time.</p><h3 class="title green mb-4">What adoption services are available for birthmothers in Eldersburg?</h3><p>Our personalized services ensure you are properly supported and fully in control throughout your entire adoption journey. Whether you’ve already decided on adoption or are just starting to research your options, our birthmother coordinators will provide you with the resources and support you need.</p><ul> <li class=mb-3>Get free services and support through the entire adoption process and beyond</li> <li class=mb-3>Choose from hundreds of loving families legally approved to adopt a baby</li> <li class=mb-3>Connect with a licensed adoption professional in your area</li> </ul> </div> </section><section class=you-arenot-alone><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col><h2 class=module-title>For more information,<br>call or text us anytime at <a href=tel:2244100522 style=display:inline-block;color:inherit>224-410-0522</a></h2></div></div></div></section><section class=loving-decision><div class=container><h3 class="title green mb-4">How do I place my baby for adoption in Eldersburg?</h3><p>Our process allows us to provide caring and compassionate support to expectant mothers wherever they are. Here’s what the adoption process looks like in your area:</p><ul class=steps> <li class=step-1><h4 class="heading green">Step 1: Learn about adoption.</h4><p>When you reach out to us, an adoption coordinator will be happy to answer any questions you have and give you all the information you need in order to decide whether adoption is right for you and your baby. Always remember that you are free to explore adoption at your own pace and you can change your mind at any point during the process up until the placement is legally finalized.</p></li> <li class=step-2><h4 class="heading green">Step 2: Choose an adoptive family.</h4><p>Your coordinator will ask you questions about what you’re looking for in an adoptive family. We work with all different types of families, including LGBT families, husband-and-wife couples, and single parents. We will present you with a selection of families that fit the unique wants and needs of you and your baby. You can communicate with as many families as you’d like.</p></li> <li class=step-3><h4 class="heading green">Step 3: Create your adoption plan.</h4><p>There are three different types of adoption plans to choose from. An open adoption is where the adoptive parents and birth parents communicate openly during and after the adoption process through text, calls, video chats, letters, emails, photos, and in-person visits. A semi-open adoption is like an open adoption but does not include in-person visits. In a closed adoption, there is no communication between the adoptive parents and the birth parents.</p></li> <li class=step-4><h4 class="heading green">Step 4: Place your baby with the family.</h4><p>As soon as you’re ready for them to do so, the adoptive family will travel to you. After the birth, you can spend as much time as you’d like with your baby and the adoptive family and you will eventually be asked to sign the necessary adoption paperwork. The baby can leave the hospital with the adoptive family and they will remain in your area until they are legally allowed to take the baby home.</p></li> </ul> </div> </section><section class="you-arenot-alone light"><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col><h2 class="module-title mb-4">How much does it cost to choose adoption as a birthmother in Eldersburg?</h2><p>As a prospective birthmother, all of our adoption services are completely free to you. Any attorneys, case workers, and service providers associated with your adoption plan will be paid for entirely by the adoptive family you connect with. In fact, part of your adoption plan will include receiving financial assistance for pregnancy-related expenses from the adoptive family. Your service provider will determine how much financial support you’re allowed to receive based on state law and your personal situation. Qualifying expenses usually include:</p><ul class="circles row"> <li class="col-md-4 rent">Rent or housing</li> <li class="col-md-4 groceries">Groceries</li> <li class="col-md-4 clothes">Maternity clothes</li> <li class="col-md-4 phone">Phone & utilities</li> <li class="col-md-4 transportation">Transportation</li> <li class="col-md-4 medical">Medical bills & counseling</li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> </section><div class=hoping-slider-mod><div class=container><h3 class="module-title mb-4">Are there adoptive families available in Eldersburg?</h3><p class=mb-5>We encourage prospective birthmothers to take part in choosing an adoptive family for their baby. We have many families across the country and in your area that are waiting to adopt, so you will have plenty of wonderful families to choose from. Each of our waiting families has gone through an extensive home study process in order to become legally allowed to adopt a baby, including educational classes, interviews, FBI background checks, home inspections, and more. You can be assured that each family we work with would be ready and willing to provide your baby with a safe and loving home and environment in which to grow and thrive.</p></div><div class="container no-padding"><ul class=hoping-slider> <li class=slide><div class=frame onclick="window.open('/profile/april-jamie/')"> <img class="profile-image jspeed-img-lazyload" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyNTAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDAwIj48L3N2Zz4=" data-jspeed-lazyload=1 loading=lazy data-src=https://hwx803o7.cdn.imgeng.in/storage/families/1591/cropped_thumb_med_new%20ab%20outus.jpeg alt=""> <div class=bottom><h6>April & Jamie</h6> <a href=javascript:void(0);>View Family Profile</a> </div></div></li> <li class=slide><div class=frame onclick="window.open('/profile/kim-jo/')"> <img class="profile-image jspeed-img-lazyload" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyNTAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDAwIj48L3N2Zz4=" data-jspeed-lazyload=1 loading=lazy data-src=https://hwx803o7.cdn.imgeng.in/storage/families/1946/cropped_thumb_med_1-about%20us.jpeg alt=""> <div class=bottom><h6>Kim & Jo</h6> <a href=javascript:void(0);>View Family Profile</a> </div></div></li> <li class=slide><div class=frame onclick="window.open('/profile/billy-michael/')"> <img class="profile-image jspeed-img-lazyload" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyNTAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDAwIj48L3N2Zz4=" data-jspeed-lazyload=1 loading=lazy data-src=https://hwx803o7.cdn.imgeng.in/storage/families/1646/cropped_thumb_med_1-about%20us.jpeg alt=""> <div class=bottom><h6>Billy & Michael</h6> <a href=javascript:void(0);>View Family Profile</a> </div></div></li> <li class=slide><div class=frame onclick="window.open('/profile/jerome-karl/')"> <img class="profile